There may weread his zeal truly ballanc'd with profound knowledge, piety, and modeſty; his grief for the ruines of Gods Church, and his people; his care for his friends; his charity for this enemies; his commiſeration of others, and courage in his own afflictions: and in all ſo even a temper;

that never any came nearer him, who at his Croſs did ſay,Luk. 23.34. 
               Father forgive them, for they know not what they do.
